I'm generously giving this location 2 stars simply because the food was delicious and the cashier was nice. However the line service was terrible. The girl making my bowl kept shooting me dirty looks every time I asked for something, like extra rice or tortillas on the side. It's not like I was asking for extra meat. I thought I was imagining the rude glaces since they were very busy, so I was nice and said my "thank you's" with a smile. My husband was ordering behind me and he overheard her call me a b-word. When he tried to ask for extra tortillas she told him no. He mentioned that I was able to get tortillas, then they reluctantly gave him one tortilla. He asked for fajitas and she said they were out even though he could clearly see the fajitas behind the glass. I've worked at Chipotle in the past and I know for a fact that you're allowed to ask for extra anything for free, except for meat and guac. Sometimes the managers would tell us to be light handed with our portions, but if the customer asks for extra you give them extra. It's not against company policy. Looking at past reviews, I'm not the first person to have issues with their portioning. I'm hoping one of the store or district managers will see this. I understand the need to reduce costs and regulate portion control. But there's no need to be so rude when a customer asks for something Chipotle is so well known for.
